11:23.884 --> 11:25.853
Oh! (laughs) Yeah.

11:25.886 --> 11:27.087
-Huh?
-Yeah.

11:27.120 --> 11:28.488
What the hell, Frank?
Where's Mac?

11:28.521 --> 11:30.157
-Mac's out.
-Why?!

11:30.190 --> 11:31.524
-Well, I think he's
going back in the closet.
-Goddamn it.

11:31.558 --> 11:33.994
You had one job: get the gay man
to dance on the gay float.

11:34.027 --> 11:35.228
-I know. No, he's, he...
-It's not that hard.

11:35.262 --> 11:36.429
We got a problem.
We got a problem.

11:36.463 --> 11:37.697
Dennis doesn't want to drive.

11:37.731 --> 11:39.032
Now he's saying
he's claustrophobic under there.

11:39.066 --> 11:40.267
What is Cricket doing here?

11:40.300 --> 11:41.534
-DEE: Because Frank blew it!
-Aw, come on, man.

11:41.568 --> 11:43.503
-You had one job to do.
-That's what I said.

11:43.536 --> 11:45.405
Cricket's gonna do the dance.
Dance, Cricket. Go. Dance.

11:45.438 --> 11:47.841
No. No, no, no. He look...
Oh, God. No! Come on, man.

11:47.875 --> 11:50.343
-No.
-He looks like a monster,
and you look like a monster.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.846
We're not trying to invite
a bar full of monster men.

11:52.880 --> 11:54.848
We're-we're looking
for high-spending gay men.

11:54.882 --> 11:56.083
Yeah, but get Dennis to dance.

11:56.116 --> 11:57.250
You can't get
the straight man to dance.

11:57.284 --> 11:58.685
The press would murder us.

11:58.718 --> 12:00.387
The press doesn't give two shits
about us.

12:00.420 --> 12:02.355
Frank, it's 2018,
and you're the only person

12:02.389 --> 12:04.091
who doesn't seem
to understand gay culture.

12:04.124 --> 12:05.425
That's true. That's true.

12:05.458 --> 12:07.627
My head is swelling with blood.

12:07.660 --> 12:09.229
Goddamn it, Charlie. We got to
be there in 20 minutes.

12:09.262 --> 12:10.430
-All right. You know what?
-(Frank groaning)

12:10.463 --> 12:11.765
Um, Cricket, fine.
You can dance. Let's go.

12:11.799 --> 12:13.033
-Yo.
-Frank, can you at least

12:13.066 --> 12:14.434
-drive the thing? Let's go.
-Yeah. All right.

12:14.467 --> 12:15.969
-Yes.
-You're driving.
You'll squeeze in there.

12:16.003 --> 12:18.371
-You drive.
-Come on, man.
-Uh, no, no, no, no, no.

12:18.405 --> 12:21.875
Lady, I'm not going anywhere
until I see an Abraham Lincoln.

12:21.909 --> 12:23.944
Here you go.

12:23.977 --> 12:25.278
What is this? What is this?

12:25.312 --> 12:28.215
-Like, 73 cents.
-No. I-I said Abraham Lincoln.

12:28.248 --> 12:30.250
-There's a bunch of Lincolns
in there.
-Oh, those are pennies!

12:30.283 --> 12:31.785
-Okay. You want
to give it back to me?
-Well, no. Hold on.

12:31.819 --> 12:33.320
-Okay, you're gonna do it?
-Yeah, I'll do it.

12:33.353 --> 12:35.222
-Yes, of course I'll do it.
(scoffs)
-Then go do it. Go!

12:35.255 --> 12:36.423
-(grunts)
-(door squeaks closed)

12:36.456 --> 12:37.657
All right, now wait a second.

12:37.690 --> 12:38.892
How do you turn it on?
First the lights.

12:38.926 --> 12:40.293
-(engine starts)
-What is that?

12:40.327 --> 12:42.062
Oh, that must be...

12:42.095 --> 12:44.131
Okay, let's see
what we got here.

12:44.164 --> 12:47.134
Okay, uh,
"Start north on Second Street.

12:47.167 --> 12:51.004
Turn right on...
Dickens Avenue."

12:51.038 --> 12:52.840
Straight to... What the...?

12:52.873 --> 12:56.176
Oh. Oh, shit. I... (groans)

12:56.209 --> 12:59.446
Oh, God. Oh, this is ridiculous.

12:59.479 --> 13:01.915
Oh, shit, I can't do this.

13:01.949 --> 13:04.918
You know what? Screw this.

13:04.952 --> 13:06.920
No good.

13:06.954 --> 13:09.089
-(knocking)
-FRANK: Mac?

13:09.122 --> 13:10.690
-Mac?
-(knocking)

13:10.723 --> 13:12.625
Mac, come here.
Let me in. Let me in.

13:12.659 --> 13:14.661
-I'm gonna break the door down!
-(woman speaking on TV)

13:14.694 --> 13:19.499
One. Two. Three.

13:19.532 --> 13:21.168
Whoa. Ah, sh...

13:21.201 --> 13:23.636
Ah, shit!

13:23.670 --> 13:26.439
Jesus, Frank, that's a lot of
blood. Is that from just now?

13:26.473 --> 13:29.209
Oh, no. No, that's from earlier.

13:29.242 --> 13:32.612
You-you see, Mac, I've been
in agony the whole day,

13:32.645 --> 13:34.814
but I came to this realization

13:34.848 --> 13:37.284
that sometimes
you got to let the blood flow

13:37.317 --> 13:39.119
in order to start the healing.

13:39.152 --> 13:41.821
Some cuts
you just can't plug up.

13:41.855 --> 13:45.025
That's the same for you.
You got this thing inside you,

13:45.058 --> 13:47.394
and you're trying to plug it up.

13:47.427 --> 13:49.496
But you got
to let that shit out.

13:49.529 --> 13:51.164
You got to let it flow.

13:51.198 --> 13:54.001
Otherwise you're gonna be in
agony for the rest of your life.

13:54.034 --> 13:56.836
So you're saying
that if I dance on the float,

13:56.870 --> 13:58.471
that maybe I'll find my pride?

13:58.505 --> 14:01.074
No. No, forget the float.

14:01.108 --> 14:03.443
That's just doing it
for the wrong reasons.

14:04.945 --> 14:06.779
You got to do something else.

14:10.717 --> 14:11.818
FRANK:
I got you a couple things

14:11.851 --> 14:13.220
from the float that you can use.

14:13.253 --> 14:14.754
I paid off the warden.

14:14.787 --> 14:16.756
They think they're seeing
a Blake Shelton concert,

14:16.789 --> 14:18.758
and I put your dad
in the front row.

14:18.791 --> 14:20.227
All right, I just...

14:20.260 --> 14:22.362
I just don't know
if I can do this, Frank.

14:22.395 --> 14:24.697
Mac, I don't get it,
and I may never get it,

14:24.731 --> 14:27.334
but I do know
you got to do this.

14:27.367 --> 14:30.370
You said you want
to tell your dad your way.

14:31.738 --> 14:33.873
So, now, do it.

14:33.907 --> 14:35.508
(exhales)

14:35.542 --> 14:38.245
Yeah. Yeah.

14:39.246 --> 14:40.213
(indistinct chatter)

14:40.247 --> 14:41.781
Hello, gentlemen.

14:41.814 --> 14:43.516
Dudes.

14:43.550 --> 14:45.085
Unfortunately...

14:45.118 --> 14:48.355
Blake Shelton
will not be making it today.

14:48.388 --> 14:51.524
-(all groaning)
-But, uh, he did send me
in his stead,

14:51.558 --> 14:54.294
and I've got something special
to show you.

14:54.327 --> 14:57.864
-Uh, my name
is Ronald McDonald, and...
-(laughter)

14:57.897 --> 15:01.134
(laughs):
I named him that.

15:01.168 --> 15:03.971
I got something
that I got to tell you, Dad,

15:04.004 --> 15:07.240
and I've been trying to find
the best way to do it, and...

15:07.274 --> 15:09.576
(sighs) I just thought
instead of saying it,

15:09.609 --> 15:13.580
maybe I could just show you
how I feel inside.

15:16.183 --> 15:18.151
Dad...

15:18.185 --> 15:20.187
I'm gay.

15:23.523 --> 15:25.525
(thunder rumbles)

15:27.427 --> 15:29.362
(rain falling)

15:31.965 --> 15:33.967
("Varú " by Sigur Rós playing)

